external_knowledge:
- The ages 40 to 60 can be considered middle-aged; 
- Private sector workers are those who work for private companies, as opposed to the government or non-profit organizations; 
- Working more than 30 hours a week is generally considered full-time employment.

- High school graduate refers to an individual who has completed high school education; 
- Local government employment refers to jobs within local government agencies; 
- 'Own-child' relationship status might imply an individual who has children of their own but still receives support or is considered dependent in some contexts; 
- Net capital gain or loss is calculated as (capital gain - capital loss); 
- Average hours worked per week > 30 implies a full-time or nearly full-time work schedule.

sql:
SELECT individual_id, SUM(capital_gain) AS total_capital_gain
FROM capital_gain_loss
GROUP BY individual_id;
